	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Distraught parents of a three-year-old girl are offering a
R30 000 reward for any information that leads to the safe return of the
toddler. According to East
Coast Radio, Little Siphesihle Dlamini went missing during
a New Year’s Eve church service in Amandawe, in the Silengeni Ward, Durban. The tot was wearing a pink dress with stripes at the time
of her disappearance. "The three-year-old child reported missing at
Amandawe, in the Silengeni area is still missing. The police continue looking
for the child,” Local police officer, Thembeka Mbhele says. “We also appeal to the community - whoever has knowledge of
the child's whereabouts to please contact police, Umzinto Child Protection or
contact the Crimestop number.” Her heartbroken father, Mxolisi Ngwane says the family has
hired a private investigator and is hopeful that they will find the little
girl. "There is a private investigator involved and we have
met with him. She's been missing since the beginning of the year,” says
Mxolisi. “It's [hard] for the family but we are hanging in there
because of the support and all the prayers.” If you have any information on the whereabouts of the little
girl, please contact Siphesihle’s father on: 084 955 5887 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  